0639 \"\u0627\u0644\u0648\u0642\u062a\": \u0644\u0648 \u0648\u062c\u062f\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0635\u062d\u0648\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0634\u0631\u064a\u0646\u0627\u062a \u0623\u0648 \u0627\u0644\u062b\u0644\u0627\u062b\u064a\u0646\u0627\u062a \u0644\u0645\u0627 \u0643\u0627\u0646 \u0644\u0647\u0627 \u0635\u062f\u0649 \u0643\u0628\u064a\u0631 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0628\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0646\"</a> &#91;Author Nader Kadhim in a lengthy interview with \"<i>Al-Waqt</i>\": If the Islamic Revival was present at the Twenties or Thirties, it would not have had made a significant impact in Bahrain&#93;. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Al-Waqt\" title=\"Al-Waqt\">Al-Waqt</a></i> (in Arabic). <a href=\"/wiki/Bahrain_Online\" title=\"Bahrain Online\">Bahrain Online</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2 April</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Al-Waqt&amp;rft.atitle=%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%AA%D8%A8+%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B1+%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B8%D9%85+%D9%81%D9%8A+%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1+%D9%85%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%84+%D9%85%D8%B9+%22%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D9%82%D8%AA%22%3A+%D9%84%D9%88+%D9%88%D8%AC%D8%AF%D8%AA+%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B5%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%A9+%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9+%D9%81%D9%8A+%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA+%D8%A3%D9%88+%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AB%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AB%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AA+%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7+%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86+%D9%84%D9%87%D8%A7+%D8%B5%D8%AF%D9%89+%D9%83%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%B1+%D9%81%D9%8A+%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%86&amp;rft.date=2007-08-12&amp;rft.au=Fadhel+Adnan&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbahrainonline.org%2Fshowthread.php%3Ft%3D182470&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANader+Kadhim\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\">